	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=64677"><span id="Sage">xaanru</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">3239 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Good [3.89]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Its only all about mana regen, if all you do is grind one group content. Quite frankly, when on a raid, my mana regen only has a trivial effect on whether I run OOM or not. We have plenty of time between mobs to med back up. What makes all the difference in the world, is that I have a large enough mana pool to chain cast heals until the mob dies.<br/><br/>So, as you see, its really all a matter of perspective. For your style of play, mana regen matters more, because it reduces downtime between mobs. For my style of play, mana POOL matters more, because I use mana a LOT faster than I can regen it, when healing a raid tank.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
